Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel @garlic{1%clove}; place whole clove in the center of a small piece of
#foil{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cinch
into a packet.

Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Trim and discard woody bottom
ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Thinly slice @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Place garlic foil packet on same baking sheet. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes
and garlic foil packet out across entire baking sheet; roast on top rack.)

Roast on middle rack for ~{15%minutes} (you'll add the asparagus then).

Once potatoes and garlic have roasted ~{15%minutes}, remove baking sheet{} from
oven. Carefully add asparagus to empty side; toss with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes and garlic
roasting; add asparagus to a second baking sheet.)

Return to middle rack until garlic is softened and veggies are browned and
tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more. (For 4, roast asparagus on middle rack.)

While veggies cook, pat @sirloin steak{14%ounce} very dry with #paper towels{};
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Once garlic is done, carefully transfer to a cutting board and mash clove with
a #fork{} until smooth.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add
garlic (start with half and add more from there if desired); cook for
~{30%seconds}.

Add @beef demi-glace{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until slightly thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in another @butter{1%tablespoon} and any resting juices from steak. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice steak against the grain. Toss potatoes with half the chives.

Divide potatoes, asparagus, and steak between plates. Top steak and potatoes
with sauce. Garnish potatoes with remaining chives and serve.

> For 4 servings, increase butter to 2 TBSP each time and water to 1/3 cup.

> "Fond" refers to the crispy bits and drippings left by the seared steak in
the pan - this is what gives the sauce its depth of flavor.